.ds n) explain_setresgid_or_die
.TH explain_setresgid_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_setresgid_or_die \- set r/e/s group ID and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_setresgid_or_die(3)" \
    "set real, effective and saved group ID and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/setresgid.h>
.sp 0.3
void explain_setresgid_or_die(gid_t rgid, gid_t egid, gid_t sgid);
.br
int explain_setresgid_on_error(gid_t rgid, gid_t egid, gid_t sgid);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_setresgid_or_die\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call. On failure an explanation will be printed
to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_setresgid\fP(3) function,
and then the process terminates by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_setresgid_on_error\fP function is used to call the
\f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call. On failure an explanation will be printed
to \f[I]stderr\fP, obtained from the \f[I]explain_setresgid\fP(3) function,
but still returns to the caller.
.TP 8n
\f[I]rgid\fP
The rgid, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]egid\fP
The egid, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]sgid\fP
The sgid, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH RETURN VALUE
The \f[B]explain_setresgid_or_die\fP function only returns on success, see
\f[I]setresgid\fP(2) for more information. On failure, prints an
explanation and exits, it does not return.
.PP
The \f[B]explain_setresgid_on_error\fP function always returns the value
return by the wrapped \f[I]setresgid\fP(2) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SH EXAMPLE
The \f[B]explain_setresgid_or_die\fP function is intended to be used in a
fashion similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
explain_setresgid_or_die(rgid, egid, sgid);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
